.TH "amdgpu_ttm_set_buffer_funcs_status" 9 "amdgpu_ttm_set_buffer_funcs_status" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_ttm_set_buffer_funcs_status \- enable/disable use of buffer functions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" amdgpu_ttm_set_buffer_funcs_status
.BI "(struct amdgpu_device *adev "  ","
.BI "bool enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
amdgpu_device pointer
.IP "enable" 12
true when we can use buffer functions.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Enable/disable use of buffer functions during suspend/resume. This should
only be called at bootup or when userspace isn't running.
